\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Model (Wolf potential).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In our model, we have used the Wolf potential 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Wolfetal"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 plus pairwise repulsive soft-core interactions,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\beta\mathcal{U}_{WF}}{K}=\frac{B_{ij}}{r^{9}}+\frac{1}{2}\sum_{i=1}^{N}\sum_{j\neq i}^{N}V_{WF}(r_{ij})-\left(\frac{\text{erfc}(\alpha r_{c})}{2r_{c}}+\frac{\alpha}{\pi^{1/2}}\right)\sum_{i=1}^{N}z_{i}^{2}\;,
\]

\end_inset

with
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{WF}(r_{ij})=\begin{cases}
z_{i}z_{j}\left(\frac{\text{erfc}(\alpha r_{ij})}{2r_{ij}}-\frac{\text{erfc}(\alpha r_{c})}{r_{c}}\right)\,, & r_{ij}\leq r_{c}\\
0\quad, & r_{ij}>r_{c}
\end{cases}\;,
\]

\end_inset

 here 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 is the Wolf screening parameter 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Wolfetal"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, which is taken as 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=4/L$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 is the simulation box, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{c}$
\end_inset

 is the cut-off radius, 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the valence.
 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is an adjustable parameter 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "PEREZHERNANDEZ2023123106"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
HNC Approximation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The hyper-netted chain (HNC) approximation is a closure for the Ornstein-Zernike
 (OZ) equation.
 For multi-component mixtures, the OZ equation reads
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h_{ij}(r)=c_{ij}+\sum_{k}\rho_{k}\int h_{ik}(|\boldsymbol{r}-\boldsymbol{r}'|)c_{kj}(\boldsymbol{r}')d\boldsymbol{r}'
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $h(r)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c(r)$
\end_inset

 are the total and direct correlation functions, respectively.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
A general closure relation between 
\begin_inset Formula $h(r)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c(r)$
\end_inset

 for the OZ equation is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\ln\left[h_{ij}(r)+1\right]=-\beta u_{ij}(r)+h_{ij}(r)-c_{ij}(r)+\mathcal{B}_{ij}(r)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}_{ij}(r)$
\end_inset

 is in literature known as the ''bridge function'' and cannot be written
 in closed form.
 Within the HNC approximation, the bridge function is taken as zero.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
